04555nam a22006495i 9780674275065DE-B159720220131112047.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220131t20222001mau    fo  d z      eng d  a97806742750657 a10.4159/97806742750652doi  a(DE-B1597)613933  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  amaucUS-MA 4aRA781.65b.M36 2001 7aHEA0070002bisacsh04a613.7/0451 aManson, JoAnn, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut14aThe 30-Minute Fitness Solution :bA Four-Step Plan for Women of All Ages /cJoAnn Manson. 1aCambridge, MA : bHarvard University Press, c[2022] 4c©2001  a1 online resource (304 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tPreface -- tContents -- tIntroduction -- t1 The Best Investment You’ll Ever Make -- t2 Exercise, Nature’s Medicine -- t3 Four Steps to a New Exercise Habit: An Overview -- t4 Step 1: Plan Your Active Lifestyle -- t5 Step 2: Proceed with Your Exercise Program -- t6 Step 3: Record Your Progress -- t7 Step 4: Reward Your Efforts -- t8 Three Strength-Training Workouts -- t9 Home Equipment and Health Clubs -- t10 Eating Your Way to Good Health -- t11 The Scientific Case for Physical Activity -- t12 Exercise for Women with Chronic Health Conditions -- t13 Working the Body, Healing the Mind -- t14 Fitness at Each Stage of Your Life -- t15 Sharing the Wealth of Good Health -- tReferences and Additional Resources -- tAcknowledgments -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aJust 30 minutes a day of moderate exercise--even walking--can save your life. This is the powerful message that Dr. JoAnn Manson--of the lead investigators of both the Women's Health Initiative and the Nurses' Health Study--and her coauthor Patricia Amend want to send to American women. Regardless of the barriers you may face--too busy, too tired, too "down," or too old--with this four-step practical plan you'll find the excuses falling away and a happier, healthier self emerging. This book offers not only state-of-the-art information from recent medical research but step-by-step instructions on how to get started and maintain a physically active lifestyle. The authors will help you choose a "core" activity that doesn't disrupt your daily life. Then they will show you how to measure your fitness level at the start, how to monitor your progress over time, and how to reward yourself for your efforts. These four simple steps to fitness will work no matter who you are--25 or 75, harried mother or overworked professional (or both), in good health or living with a chronic disease. The authors have included a clearly illustrated program of stretching and strength-training exercises; sensible activities for women with health concerns; an intelligent weight-loss plan; guidelines for selecting home exercise equipment and choosing a health club; and much more. With over 100 illustrations, questionnaires, and checklists, this book has everything you need to feel good, look better, and live longer, starting today--it's all just 30 minutes away.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aFitness walking. 0aPhysical fitness for women. 0aWalkingxHealth aspects. 0aWomenxHealth and hygiene. 7aHEALTH & FITNESS / Exercise.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674275065zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674275065423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674275065/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MDPM  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MDPM  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK